caption: This spot never fails to impress. They serve good food for fair rates, there is no waiting time even when they are busy.

I had the smoked briskets sandwich with a side of Mac & cheese and Brussels sprouts. It was absolutely delicious. The Mac & cheese was on point 👏 the service was fantastic. Definitely going back

I've been here several times for brunch. I love the beer cheese with pretzel loaf and I get the steak skewers and the side salad and combine them to make a steak salad. So good and really spicy! It's not the place to go if you want a really loud/party brunch, but the food is always so delicious and they have bottomless Mimosas, beermosas and beer. Plus, I've never not been able to get a table for brunch even at the last minute.

Exceptional establishment! My husband and I stopped in for dinner on a Saturday night and shared a few appetizers. We had the mac n cheese with bacon, beer cheese and homemade chips, and the short rib turnover, all of which were amazing! It was the perfect amount for the two of us. The beer selection was also fantastic, they had every kind, especially dark beers which my husband loves and not available everywhere. The selections we had are no longer on the current menu, but there is plenty to choose from.  Other than food and drink the ambiance of the whole place was fantastic. Our service was excellent, Tony was our server,  super friendly and made great suggestions. Great conversation too! Next time we stop back, we will definitely be back!

Small cozy perfect place for a winter drink. Most of their beers are from the Chicago area. Jeff, I think the owner allowed us to sample many beers before settling on our choices. Very relaxed atmosphere, great mellow music and delicious appetizers. Will definitely come back.

Low-key place that is surprisingly less crowded than most River North spots   Food is well prepared American Gastropub fare.  Fries were a bit on the salty side   The pretzel loaf was warm, crusty and very flavorful.  The beer list is the main star here - lots to pick from and many local breweries.  Service was attentive, friendly and informative. I recommend this place for anyone in River North that is looking for a chill spot to enjoy beer, decent food with friends and be able to have a conversation without having to yell to be heard.

Pros: Great atmosphere, eclectic design elements, friendly staff.  Cons: Food is way overpriced for what you get. I ordered the burger with a side salad and one drink - $35 not including tip.  The food I ordered was incorrectly made - basically, I ordered a burger medium-well, and it was rare... so rare that it was actually cold in the middle. I brought this to the attention of the staff and was given the steak tips instead which were super spicy, but overall had good flavor.  Definitely an experience, but a once-in-your-lifetime experience that you don't necessarily want to try again.

I wanted to try a bunch of the stuff they had on tap but the only ones they offered as tasters were the more generic ones. Overall it’s a great beer bar.

First of all, this is a great looking place with an amazing selection of beer and very friendly staff. However we went there two times and each time the food was disappointing. Especially yesterday where we ordered two burgers (which were definitely not the best burgers in the neighborhood, but that just my taste). The BIG issue here is we received a plateful of very salty fries with our food. We didn't wanted fries with a side of burger, more the other way around. We barely even finished half of it, our mouths burning with salt and feeling that it just a huge waste of food.  So I can forgive food that is not to my taste. But wasting good food should not be tolerable and hopefully should be easy to fix at this otherwise great beerhall. And easy on the salt please !

Went in for dinner after reading all the good reviews and discovered that this place is overhyped. My friend and I were very hungry when we stopped in and usually that means that we’ll find anything delicious. We’re not picky eaters at all. But nope, the food was merely okay. It wasn’t bad but there also wasn’t anything good about it.  We ordered the Brussels sprouts, pulled madras chicken and the burger with fries. The Brussels sprouts were fine but there wasn’t anything particularly special about them. The pulled madras chicken flatbread was underwhelming in taste and strange because the chicken was bland and the spicy seasoning was put in the yogurt sauce on it. Anyone who’s cooked anything would know that seasoning belongs on the chicken and the yogurt should act as something to cool down the spice. And the burger was nothing special either, it was an $8 burger being sold for $15. My friend would’ve been happier with five guys. The fries were also bland and not memorable.  Their one strength is that the beer selection is very good but that’s not unique to this place, so I won’t be back.

Went here for their special Founders CBS and KBS beer tapping event.  If you love beer, this is the place for you.  They have a huge selection of different crafted beers.  The CVS and KBS beers are 12 and $14. However the rest of the draft beers are price anywhere from $4 to $12.  The decor is rustic with a long wooden bar and a long wooden communal table in the back.  The front section has tables and booths for your dining pleasure.  There is also an outdoor eating area in the front of the restaurant that is open weather permitting.  We shared an order of steamed mussels with  curried sausage,  wittekerke Belgian beer, potato, and baguette, which was $16 and filling enough for two.  The food menu has some interesting choices on it such as Krispy Kreme sausage crepes and the house charcuterie which consists of tasso ham, smoked duck breast, smoked liver sausage, duck prosciutto, and summer sausage.  It was very busy that night and it was impossible to get the bartender's attention, I had to grab a waitress as she was running past me in order to place my order.  A nice casual Eatery you can meet friends at and enjoy different choices of food while you enjoy your beer!
